Title : Sakumtha River
Text : The '''Sakumtha River''' is a  [[river]] in [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], flowing south out of the [[Kitimat Ranges]] from an origin west of the [[Tsaydaychuz Peak]] massif into the [[Dean River]] north of [[Bella Coola, British Columbia|Bella Coola]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/13608.html BC Names entry "Sakumtha River"]</ref>

==Name origin==
"Sakumtha" is from the [[Kimsquit]] dialect of the [[Nuxalk language]] and means "to wade across".<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/13608.html BC Names entry "Sakumtha River"]</ref>

